WHETHER or not the filly Genuuine Risk beats or even com  petes against colts in the Travers Stakes at Saratoga later this month, her victory in last May's Kentucky Derby has invoked a subtle but compelling challenge to top-flight female athletes in other sports.
headline_main: Can Women and Men Compete?; Physical Isn't Athletic

abstract: WHEN modernists have not been busy mystifying their audience, they have insisted on making it see with  fresh eyes ideas and shapes that normally are taken for granted. So much so, that the notion of nothing being what it seems to be has itself come to be taken for granted, which makes it, too, a cliche worthy of re-examination.

BOSTON--An overlooked factor in this season of the volatile voter is gender. Primary polls indicate that there have been twice as many women as men in the "undecided" column. Since the single most potent force of the past primary year has been the "undecideds," a key question is why are more women than men undecided?
THE Munich Dance Project (Tanzprojekt Munchen), a modern-dance group from West Germany, made its local debut Tuesday night at the Performing Garage, 33 Wooster Street, for a run through tomorrow.
